<h4><small>2. Wrap line at x characters</small></h4>




<small>
Some DivX hardware players displays the subtitles at a fixed font size.
This means that if the text lines are too long some characters will be
displayed outside the TV screen! In the preferences you can ask
SubCleaner to break the lines at a fixed character number. You have to
try to see the value that fits better your case. For example with my
LinkTheater device 50 characters is a good value.<br>




<br>




