<h4><small>3. Limit&nbsp;to x lines</small></h4>


<small>Some DivX hardware players can display only a fixed numbers of
line. This function will try to fit the subtitle on a limited number of
lines using if necessary a max number of characters per line.<br>


<br>


If this is not possible, it will split the subtitle and display with a timing related to the number of lines.<br>
<br>
</small>
<h4><small>4. Remove style tags</small></h4>


<small>Some DivX hardware players don't understand the style tags
(&lt;i&gt;,&lt;b&gt;,...). This function will recognize these types of
tags and will remove it from the text.</small>

<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p>




